My dot vim to develop app using Ruby or Ruby on Rails. Inspired by http://github.com/xinuc/dotvim

Usage:
1. Download to your home directory and rename to .vim/
2. Create symbolic link to .vim/.vimrc
% cd ~
% ln -s .vim/.vimrc .vimrc


Plugins:
1. NERD_tree
2. rails.vim
3. SnipMate.vim
4. vim-surround
5. vim-endwise
6. haml.vim

Example:
% vim example.txt

Shorcuts in command mode:
1. Press Shift + Tab to toggle NERD_tree
2. Press i on NERD_tree to open below current file
3. ctrl+h = left tab
4. ctrl+j = down tab
5. ctrl+k = right
6. ,p = copy from clipboard

Available colorscheme:
1. http://www.vi-improved.org/color_sampler_pack/
2. twilight2
